Ground Beef Broccoli Stir Fry
  --Laurel Randolph

1 c water
6 tbsp lower-sodium shoyu
3 tbsp packed light brown sugar
1 tbsp cornstarch
3 cloves garlic, minced
1 tbsp minced fresh ginger (from 1" piece)
2 tsp unseasoned rice vinegar
3 tbsp neutral oil (such as canola), divided
12 oz (~5 1/4 c) fresh broccoli florets
1 lb 90/10 lean ground beef 
1/2 tsp kosher salt
2 tsp toasted sesame seeds (optional)
2 green onions, thinly sliced (optional)
steamed white rice, for serving

Whisk together the water, soy sauce, brown sugar, cornstarch, garlic, ginger, and rice vinegar in a medium bowl until combined and the sugar is dissolved. Set aside. Heat 2 tbsp of the oil in a large nonstick skillet over medium-high until shimmering. Add the broccoli and cook, stirring occasionally, until tender-crisp and blackened in spots, 6-7 min. Transfer broccoli to a large bowl; set aside. Reduce the heat to medium and add the remaining 1 tbsp of oil to the skillet. Add the ground beef and sprinkle with salt. Cook, stirring occasionally to break the meat into crumbles, until browned, ~5 min. Add the sauce. Bring to a simmer and cook, stirring constantly, until sauce thickens slightly and flavors meld, ~3 min. Return the broccoli to the skillet and cook, stirring constantly, until the sauce has thickened and evenly coats meat and vegetables,~3 min. Top with sesame seeds and green onions (if using). Serve over steamed white rice. 


Notes: can use broth instead of water for more flavor, can add other veggies (or swap) eg bell pepper, carrots, etc. other toppings: chopped peanuts, cilantro, etc
